cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper primarily deals with semantic scene segmentation in videos, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves joint-learning and exploring the contribution of different representations, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of the MIT Driving Scene Segmentation dataset and the focus on dynamic scene segmentation suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.RO (Robotics and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves video processing and analysis, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
